title: 820-3332 Fails Walking Zeros & Walking Bitflip tests only.
message:
I have an 820-3332 board that seems to work fine, but consistently fails the memory tests for Walking Zeros and Walking Bitflip. The error given is, "Child process exited due to signal. Usually a crash!". There are no other errors, and the board ran Heaven GPU for 1 hour without any issues. I inspected the board and found no damage.

Is this likely to progress into total memory failure? Should I disregard since the board works fine otherwise, even though it fails the test consistently and reliably? All help/input appreciated!
